                    "@type": "Answer",
                    text: "The most common issues are BiSG pulley bearing wear in stop-start use, intake valve carbon fouling, GPF saturation from urban driving, and minor oil consumption in early builds. All are documented in JLR service bulletins and manageable with proper maintenance and driving habits.",
